text.section:
If an action or special proceeding against a State officer or State employee in which the Attorney General has declined representation under § 12-304(b)(1) of this subtitle results in final judgment, the court or jury shall find whether:
the defense of sovereign immunity is available to the officer or employee;
the officer or employee was acting within the scope of the employment of the officer or employee;
the alleged act or omission was malicious; and
the alleged act or omission was grossly negligent.
